StoryAsset.name: PreMatch League Match Up User Higher

keyValuePair.Value: Do you fancy your team's chances today?
Yourselves up against %1s, this is a massive game at the top of the table. Everybody's got an opinion about it. How do you see the game going? Can your lads come out on top?
We'll just focus on our own performance.
I'm feeling very confident. I think we've got the beating of them. But we know that, to win, we'll need to be at our absolute best. We're ready to go out and perform!
The lads are 100% ready for this.
We've had a great week in training. The lads look fresh and I know they can't wait for the game. I think we're the better team. This is our chance to go out and prove it.
We'll see who's stronger on the day.
I'm not in the mood for making any predictions. I know my players are looking forward to the game. I'm sure the opposition are, too. Let's just see what happens, shall we?
Should this be an easy three points?
You're up against the last-place team in the table today. Is the game a foregone conclusion? Maybe a chance for your team to run in a few goals?
The points are there to be won.
To be honest, we don't think about where our opponents are in the table. Three points are three points, whoever we're up against. Today's no different. We'll look to do a professional job.
I think our attitude will be right.
I have a well-drilled and very professional group of players at my disposal. They know they need to be at 100% in every game, whoever we're playing. I hope we can score a few goals.
Goal difference could be important.
The win is the important thing, of course. But %1s have been struggling lately. I've told the players already: today might be a chance to improve our goal difference.
Will you match their hunger.
We know how motivated your opponents will be. Bottom of the table, they're desperate for points right now. Are you confident that your boys will match their hunger and desire on the day?
We're as hungry as they are.
That's a ridiculous question. We're top of the table and we want to stay there. Of course we'll be as motivated as they are! We know we need to win every game.
Don't ever question my team's attitude.
This is %1s you're talking about! We're an experienced and professional team. We've got a winning mentality. You'll never need to question the boys' attitude.
We take nothing for granted.
The fact that it's top against bottom doesn't come into it for my players. We take every game seriously and respect every opponent. We'll definitely match them for motivation today.
Can this game lift you closer to top spot?
It's very competitive at the top end of the table and this looks like a very close game. Are you aware that a win could actually push you in closer behind the league leaders?
It's a six-pointer!
We're second. And we know where we want to be, come the end of the season. Points against the teams around us are so important if we want to reach the top of the table.
We'll push for top spot, for sure.
The boys are playing really well and I'm sure they're ready for this game. This is the kind of fixture we have to win if we're going to get to the top of the table. We can't wait!
It's a close one to call.
We know we're up against a very good team today. But I have to remind you that we're a very good team as well! It could be a classic. We'll just have to wait and see who comes out on top.
Are you expecting a real challenge from %1s?
This is a battle for top spot in the table, with %1s your nearest challengers. Do you expect the opposition to be even more highly-motivated and competitive today than usual?
We'll match them in every way.
We're top for a reason. My players are ready for the game, that's for sure. We're convinced we're a match for them, mentally, tactically and physically. We can't wait for kick-off.
We're ready for the challenge, I promise.
We've trained really well this week. The lads are determined to take the game to %1s. We want to put down a marker here with a win. Let's see if our opponents can find any answers.
Tough game for us. For them, too!
We know this is a big game in the season. There's top spot at stake, after all. But we've trained hard and we're ready to go out and play our football. Let's see which team handles the pressure.
Are %1s a threat to your position at the top?
This is a very big game for %1s as they look to close the gap on you at the top of the table. How are your boys feeling? Do you see today's opponents as title contenders?
We have to show why we're top.
I think we're top of the table because we're the best team in the league. This is another great opportunity for us to prove that. We're looking forward to putting on a show.
It'll be a real contest, I think.
This league's so competitive. We know every opponent thinks they can knock us off our perch. Today we'll see two strong teams giving it 100%. We'll do our best to come out on top.
We respect our opponents.
I've got to say I really respect the opposition and their manager. They've done very well to keep challenging at the top end of the table. Now, though, we just want to go out and beat them!
Is complacency an issue?
You're up against %1s today, a team struggling at the wrong end of the table. Are you at all worried about complacency seeping into your dressing room?
We don't expect an easy game.
Complacency is only an issue if you think a game's going to be easy. But we're under no illusions. We won't underestimate our opponents today. The boys know they have a job to do.
I've warned the boys about underestimating anybody.
This league is very competitive. It's natural to feel more relaxed going into games against weaker teams, but we know that anyone can spring a surprise if our attitude's not right.
This league is very competitive. It's natural to feel more relaxed going into games against weaker teams, but we know that anyone can spring a surprise if our attitude's not right.
%1s's league position isn't a consideration.
I'm absolutely sure that today's opponents are far better than their league position suggests. We've got a plan for beating them and the boys will be fully committed to seeing that through.
How will you motivate your players today?
Sometimes players look at a game and don't feel the pressure, as if there's not much at stake. How do you plan to get a really committed performance out of your team here?
We have professional standards.
I hope the boys know that every game matters. Points are points, whoever you're playing against. We have to be professional in our approach every time we step onto the field.
I'm not worried about my team.
This is an experienced group of players and one thing you can never fault is their attitude. They know you can't pick and choose when to turn up. This team gives 100% in every single game.
You can't pick and choose your games.
There's something at stake in every single game we play. We can't make judgements on the basis of who we're playing. We have to go out and do our jobs every time, don't we?
